                    "name": "Ambush Hunters",
                    "type": "sidebar",
                    "sections": [],
                    "text": "Due to its size and ungainliness, a\ngraveshell must employ an unusual\nhunting strategy if it hopes to catch\na meal. A young graveshell usually\nscavenges its first lure from among\nthe animals slain by swifter and\nmore ferocious members of its kind.\nThe graveshell carefully positions its\nchosen corpse atop its shell to cover\nthe spikes that keep it in place. Then,\nthe creature sinks down into a pool\nof water, leaving only the corpse\nvisible above the surface. When\nan ignorant passerby wades into\nthe water to inspect the seemingly\nfloating cadaver, the graveshell fully\nextends its spikes to impale its latest\nvictim before using tooth and claw\nto rend its fresh catch.",
